after%20working%20for%20two%20or%20three%20days%20a%20week.%20She%20also%20spent%20more%20on%20food%20and%20shopping%20while%20traveling%20to%20different%20countries%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Tan%20works%2012%20hours%20a%20day%2C%20six%20days%20a%20week.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20have%20time%20to%20spend%20my%20money%20elsewhere%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETan%20said%20it%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etook%20time%20to%20get%20used%20to%20working%20in%20the%20147-square-foot%20stall%20space%2C%20which%20gets%20hot%20and%20stuffy%20when%20Hsu%20grills%20meat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224896%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20people%20working%20in%20a%20hawker%20stall.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d6b5b414a5cd1fcc8c884c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223264%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHawker%20stalls%20are%20often%20cramped%20and%20hot.%3Cp%3EErin%20Liam%2F%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20parents%20were%20against%20the%20career%20switch.%20%26quot%3BEven%20until%20today%2C%20they%20asked%20me%20why%20I%20had%20to%20give%20up%20a%20comfortable%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c31013cd-cce7-457a-987b-1706cffbf53a%5C%22%3ENo%20easy%20business%20to%20break%20into%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hawker%20business%20is%20challenging%20to%20succeed%20in.%20Although%20startup%20costs%20may%20be%20lower%20than%20those%20of%20other%20food%20and%20business%20enterprises%2C%20it%20is%20physically%20demanding%20and%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhawker-chan-michelin-star-bib-gourmand-hawker-restaurant-singapore-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyield%20narrow%20profits%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20guarantee%20you%20will%20succeed.%20People%20have%20failed.%20That's%20the%20reality.%20If%20you%20don't%20do%20your%20homework%20well%2C%20you%20don't%20study%20your%20menu%2C%20you%20will%20fall%20very%20fast%2C%26quot%3B%20KF%20Seetoh%2C%20a%20food%20critic%20and%20the%20founder%20of%20Urban%20Hawker%20in%20New%20York%20City%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmichelin-star-singapore-restaurant-hawker-stall-chef-nasi-lemak-food-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20BI%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EUrban%20Hawker%20is%20the%20first%20street%20food%20center%20in%20the%20US%20that%20features%20Singaporean%20hawker%20cuisine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20risks%20involved%2C%20Tan%20was%20confident%20in%20her%20decision.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20not%20really%20concerned%20about%20whether%20the%20business%20would%20succeed%20because%20I%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20faith%20in%20my%20husband%2C%26quot%3B%20Tan%20said.%20She%20met%20Hsu%20in%202014%20on%20an%20internship%20in%20Taiwan.%20The%20pair%20got%20married%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223118%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20couple%20poses%20in%20front%20of%20their%20stall%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d7ef4d289b805d1db3e760%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222754%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETan%20had%20full%20trust%20in%20her%20husband%2C%20Hsu.%3Cp%3EErin%20Liam%2F%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20they%20first%20started%20out%2C%20business%20was%20slow.%20They%20sold%20around%2050%20sets%20%E2%80%94%20which%20range%20between%20SG%24%208.50%20to%20SG%24%2013.50%20a%20piece%20%E2%80%94%20each%20day.%20They%20had%20monthly%20expenditures%20to%20consider%2C%20too%3A%20Tan%20estimates%20that%20the%20cost%20of%20operating%20the%20stall%20is%20around%20SG%2421%2C000%20monthly%2C%20including%20rent%2C%20which%20costs%20around%20SG%245%2C500.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20business%20started%20to%20look%20up%20when%20Tan's%20videos%20about%20her%20hawker%20life%20gained%20traction%20on%20TikTok.%20Local%20media%20also%20began%20to%20cover%20the%20business.%20The%20fact%20that%20the%20stall%20owner%20had%20worked%20at%20Singapore%20Airlines%20added%20a%20layer%20of%20curiosity%20and%20drew%20interest%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20visit%20to%20their%20food%20stall%20on%20a%20Friday%20afternoon%20in%20August%2C%20I%20spotted%20a%20few%20customers%20finishing%20their%20final%20bites%20of%20the%20hot%20plate%20dish.%20It%20was%20almost%20the%20end%20of%20the%20lunch%20hour%2C%20and%20the%20side%20option%20of%20bean%20sprouts%20was%20sold%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Hsu%20cooks%20the%20final%20delivery%20orders%20in%20the%20kitchen%2C%20Tan%20never%20pauses%20for%20a%20break.%20She%20helps%20to%20pack%20orders%2C%20pours%20sauce%20into%20takeaway%20packets%2C%20and%20chats%20cordially%20with%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224756%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chicken%20chop%20teppenyaki%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d7ee7f14a5cd1fcc8cf858%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223189%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20chicken%20chop%20set%20is%20priced%20at%20SG%248.50%20and%20comes%20with%20a%20grain%2C%20side%2C%20and%20sauce.%3Cp%3EErin%20Liam%2F%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETan%20said%20the%20skills%20she%20gained%20as%20a%20Singapore%20Girl%20%E2%80%94%20a%20nickname%20given%20to%20the%20airline's%20female%20flight%20attendants%20%E2%80%94%20have%20proven%20helpful%20in%20unexpected%20ways.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20used%20to%20talking%20to%20customers.%20So%2C%20as%20a%20hawker%2C%20I%20can%20make%20customers%20feel%20comfortable%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20nice.%20I%20mean%2C%20you%20don't%20really%20get%20that%20in%20hawker%20stalls%20because%20people%20usually%20just%20order%20their%20food%20and%20go%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f1fa0e0d-b920-4ba4-8ed1-a0dac6943221%5C%22%3EThe%20perks%20of%20being%20a%20hawker%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Tan%20was%20a%20flight%20attendant%2C%20she%20simply%20had%20to%20report%20for%20work%2C%20follow%20instructions%2C%20and%20get%20paid%20a%20regular%20salary%20at%20the%20end%20of%20each%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20now%2C%20Tan%20gets%20to%20be%20her%20own%20boss.%20While%20Hsu%20oversees%20cooking%2C%20Tan%20handles%20the%20cashier%2C%20administrative%20work%2C%20accounting%2C%20and%20marketing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Tan%20doesn't%20see%20herself%20returning%20to%20the%20life%20of%20flying%2C%20one%20thing%20she%20does%20miss%20is%20the%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20talking%20about%20the%20airplane%20food%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20mean%20the%20food%20overseas.%20You%20know%2C%20biryani%20in%20India%2C%20The%20Cheesecake%20Factory%20in%20the%20US%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20with%20a%20laugh.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224864%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20working%20at%20a%20hawker%20stall%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d7ede81d8d2deb96b8798b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223243%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDespite%20the%20challenges%20of%20being%20a%20hawker%2C%20Tan%20has%20found%20the%20job%20rewarding.%3Cp%3EErin%20Liam%2F%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20she%20feels%20pride%20in%20being%20part%20of%20a%20bigger%20movement%20to%20prevent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-the-michelin-list-ruined-hawker-culture-food-for-singapore-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESingapore's%20hawker%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20dying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-chicken-rice-singapore-hawker-maxwell-tian-tian-review-michelin-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehawker%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20inscribed%20on%20the%20UNESCO%20Representative%20List%20of%20the%20Intangible%20Cultural%20Heritage%20of%20Humanity.%20According%20to%20the%20National%20Environment%20Agency's%20website%2C%20the%20median%20age%20of%20hawkers%20is%2060%20%E2%80%94%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Edespite%20the%20retirement%20age%20in%20Singapore%20being%2063.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Tan%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BYou'll%20need%20a%20new%20generation%20to%20help%20the%20hawker%20culture.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20buzz%20from%20lunch%20hour%20began%20to%20wind%20down%2C%20Tan%20started%20to%20prepare%20ingredients%20for%20the%20dinner%20crowd.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20hawker%20lifestyle%20is%20challenging%2C%20but%20I%20think%20if%20more%20youngsters%20are%20willing%20to%20go%20through%20this%20process%2C%20it's%20rewarding%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflight-attendant-singapore-airlines-quit-open-hawker-stall-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725927242000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d95229289b805d1db47de1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflight-attendant-singapore-airlines-quit-open-hawker-stall-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Cherry%20Tan%2C%2029%2C%20says%20her%20parents%20weren't%20happy%20about%20her%20career%20change.%20%26quot%3BEven%20until%20today%2C%20they%20asked%20me%20why%20I%20had%20to%20give%20up%20a%20comfortable%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20BI.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22eliam%40insider.com%20(Erin%20Liam)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflight-attendant-singapore-airlines-quit-open-hawker-stall-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20Open%20attendance%20tops%20one%20million%20for%20first%20time%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725927162000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-113208688%2Cimgsize-193784.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Ftennis%2Fus-open%2Fus-open-2024-attendance-tops-one-million-for-first-time%2Farticleshow%2F113208685.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%202024%20US%20Open%20set%20a%20new%20attendance%20record%20with%20over%20one%20million%20fans%20at%20the%20Billie%20Jean%20King%20National%20Tennis%20Center.%20Taylor%20Fritz%20lost%20to%20Jannik%20Sinner%20in%20the%20men's%20final%2C%20while%20Jessica%20Pegula%20was%20defeated%20by%20Aryna%20Sabalenka%20in%20the%20women's%20final.%20The%20tournament%20had%20a%20record%20%2475%20million%20purse.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20SPORTS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20teach%20wealthy%20kids%20with%20special%20needs.%20Money%20can't%20solve%20everything%2C%20but%20it%20can%20give%20them%20the%20education%20they%20need.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Nathaniel%20Hannan%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d03ab51d8d2deb96b70ec6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAs%20a%20travel%20tutor%2C%20Nathaniel%20Hannan%20has%20taught%20students%20with%20special%20needs%20across%20the%20world.%3Cp%3ENathaniel%20Hannan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ENathaniel%20Hannan%20has%20been%20a%20travel%20tutor%20with%20Tutors%20International%20for%2018%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20that%20weaving%20travel%20into%20his%20curriculum%20has%20helped%20his%20students%20tremendously.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEnabling%20his%20students%20to%20learn%20provides%20the%20greatest%20emotional%20fulfillment%2C%20Hannan%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Nathaniel%20Hannan%2C%20a%20travel%20tutor%20at%20Tutors%20International.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20my%20time%20at%20Oxford%20in%202004%2C%20I%20faced%20two%20very%20different%20job%20offers%3A%20a%20private%20equity%20position%20and%20a%20teaching%20job%20in%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%20I%20couldn't%20see%20myself%20doing%20private%20equity%20for%2080%20hours%20a%20week.%20It%20felt%20like%20it%20would%20kill%20my%20soul%2C%20no%20matter%20the%20money%2C%20so%20I%20chose%20teaching.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20experience%20has%20been%20incredibly%20diverse%2C%20but%20almost%20all%20my%20clients%20involve%20students%20with%20special%20educational%20needs.%20This%20refers%20to%20a%20range%20of%20educational%20disabilities%2C%20from%20autism%20spectrum%20disorders%20to%20dyslexia%2C%20dysgraphia%2C%20dyscalculia%2C%20and%20anxiety%20disorders%2C%20which%20might%20not%20be%20supported%20by%20traditional%20classrooms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20never%20expected%20to%20teach%20students%20with%20special%20educational%20needs%2C%20nor%20do%20I%20have%20the%20formal%20training%20or%20credentials%20for%20it.%20But%20over%20the%20years%2C%20I've%20worked%20with%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20children%2C%20from%20those%20with%20simple%20dyslexia%20to%20a%20student%20missing%20a%20piece%20of%20his%20brain%20due%20to%20a%20motorcycle%20accident.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20family%20I%20worked%20with%20had%20two%20kids%20with%20dyslexia%20and%20attention%20deficit%20problems.%20I%20was%20with%20them%20for%20a%20year%20before%20moving%20on%20to%20other%20clients.%20Each%20child%20is%20unique%2C%20and%20there%20is%20no%20one%20way%20to%20help%20every%20student%20understand%20a%20concept.%20My%20job%20is%20to%20think%20outside%20the%20box%20and%20determine%20the%20best%20approach%20for%20each%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2227364999-0b7b-4fbe-b73f-e7f3ce4507ee%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWeaving%20traveling%20with%20tutoring%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20memorable%20job%20happened%20during%20the%20pandemic%20from%202020%20to%202023.%20I%20worked%20with%20a%20family%20in%20the%20movie%20industry%20who%20traveled%20to%20shoot%20their%20film%20across%20six%20countries.%20I%20became%20the%20child's%20school%20for%20three%20years%2C%20allowing%20her%20to%20learn%20consistently%20despite%20a%20hectic%20filming%20schedule.%20She%20had%20special%20needs%20and%20is%20now%20at%20an%20Ivy%20League%20university.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20unique%20experience%20because%20we%20were%20among%20the%20few%20people%20allowed%20to%20travel%20freely%2C%20and%20the%20only%20people%20I%20got%20to%20know%20were%20the%20actors%20traveling%20with%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20every%20job%20I've%20had%20involved%20travel%2C%20whether%20on%20a%20boat%20or%20moving%20from%20country%20to%20country.%20To%20date%2C%20I've%20lived%20in%2013%20countries.%20As%20an%20educator%2C%20it%20presents%20a%20wonderful%20opportunity%20for%20me%20because%20it%20allows%20me%20to%20interweave%20aspects%20of%20the%20local%20culture%2C%20history%2C%20and%20geography%20into%20my%20lessons.%20That's%20a%20rare%20circumstance%20in%20which%20I%20can%20help%20them%20fall%20in%20love%20with%20the%20Latin%20language%20and%20Roman%20history%20in%20a%20way%20that%20I%20just%20can't%20do%20by%20sitting%20in%20the%20family%20home%20in%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22215df387-19d6-4cd6-9f6b-4785cfd4b274%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEnabling%20children%20to%20learn%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20memory%20I%20cherish%20was%20when%20I%20spent%20a%20summer%20tutoring%20a%20dyslexic%20student%20in%20chemistry%20and%20math%20to%20prepare%20him%20for%20the%20next%20school%20year.%20As%20a%20final%20exam%2C%20I%20got%20creative%20when%20his%20dad%20panned%20gold%20dust%20from%20a%20shipwreck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20challenged%20the%20boy%20to%20figure%20out%20the%20purity%20percentage%20of%20the%20gold.%20His%20dad%20didn't%20believe%20he%20could%20do%20it%2C%20but%20after%20days%20of%20hard%20work%2C%20the%20kid%20did%20it%20and%20brought%20his%20findings%20to%20his%20dad%2C%20who%20was%20so%20moved%20he%20actually%20cried.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dad%20had%20the%20gold%20dust%20preserved%20in%20Lucite%2C%20and%20now%20it's%20a%20paperweight%20on%20his%20desk%20so%20that%20he%20can%20always%20remember%20when%20his%20son%20surprised%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20special%20thing%20to%20enable%20someone%20to%20do%20something%20they%20otherwise%20wouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20do.%20Teaching%20for%20me%20goes%20much%20deeper%20than%20just%20teaching%20people%20facts%3B%20it%20also%20involves%20showing%20them%20new%20ways%20of%20doing%20academic%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a43de9c2-0315-4597-99d8-865df1d655aa%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWealth%20is%20an%20enabler%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20clients%20I've%20worked%20with%20have%20resources%20on%20par%20with%20countries'%20governments.%20Still%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20there's%20a%20whole%20lot%20different%20about%20teaching%20students%20of%20a%20certain%20socioeconomic%20class%20%E2%80%94%20except%20that%20they%20likely%20couldn't%20afford%20to%20hire%20me%20without%20their%20resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20to%20believe%20that%20money%20was%20the%20root%20of%20all%20evil%2C%20but%20what%20money%20does%20is%20enable%20people%20to%20behave%20in%20a%20way%20that%20nobody%20else%20can.%20It%20gives%20you%20all%20the%20tools%20to%20exercise%20your%20advice%20as%20deeply%20as%20possible%20by%20removing%20many%20societal%20restrictions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20will%20do%20this%20until%20I%20no%20longer%20need%20to%20work%20for%20money.%20There%20is%20a%20children's%20cancer%20hospital%20in%20Atlanta%2C%20where%20kids%20usually%20go%20for%20six%20to%20nine%20months%20of%20treatment.%20Currently%2C%20there%20is%20no%20provision%20for%20them%20to%20continue%20their%20education%20while%20they're%20being%20treated%2C%20so%20that's%20what%20I%20am%20going%20to%20do%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3C